{"lemma":"مُظِلَّةٍ","slug":"مُظِلَّةٍ","root":"ظ.ل.ل","root_slug":"ظ-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ل-ل","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27607"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B8%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"umbrella, parasol, shade"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"parachute"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"awning, shade, alcove, canopy"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Tool noun and noun of place from the root ظ ل ل (ẓ l l)."},"ipa":["/ma.ðˤal.la/","/mi.ðˤal.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27607","headword_ar":"مِظَلَّةٌ","root":"Zl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZal~apN","text_ar":"مَظَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, Msb, K,) the former with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an instrumental noun, (Msb,) [and the latter with fet-h as a noun of place,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large tent of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats'"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more ample than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so says El-Fárábee: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the kinds of tents of the Arabs of the desert, the largest of the tents of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats'"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"next after which is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasuwT","text_ar":"وَسُوط"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and then, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the smallest of the tents of [goats'] hair; so says AZ: but Aboo-Málik says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mZl~p","text_ar":"مظلّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbA='","text_ar":"خبا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large:"},{"kind":"text","text":"IAar says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayomap","text_ar":"خَيْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of poles roofed with [the panic grass called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vamaAm","text_ar":"ثَمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is not of cloths; but the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mZl~p","text_ar":"مظلّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of cloths:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the tents called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobiyap","text_ar":"اَخْبِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is large, of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobiyap","text_ar":"اَخْبِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and it is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"only of cloths;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large, having a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riwaAq","text_ar":"رِوَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes it is of one oblong piece of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uq~ap","text_ar":"شُقَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of two such pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of three; and sometimes it has a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kifaA='","text_ar":"كِفَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is its hinder part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Th,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is peculiarly of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats'"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zul~apN","text_ar":"ظُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuloZulN","text_ar":"ظُلْظُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZaAl~u","text_ar":"مَظَالُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZaAli","text_ar":"مَظَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZaAliY","text_ar":"مَظَالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs at the end of a verse of Umeiyeh Ibn-Abee-'Áïdh El-Hudhalee, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZaAl~i","text_ar":"مَظَالِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the [latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"being either elided, or changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~apN maA Eil~apu A^awotaAdK waA^axil~apK waEamadi AlmiZal~api AuboruzuwA liSihorikumo","text_ar":"عِلَّةٌ مَا عِلَّةُ اَوْتَادٍ وَاَخِلَّةٍ وَعَمَدِ المِظَلَّةِ اُبْرُزُوا لِصِهْرِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zul~apN","text_ar":"ظُلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pretext: what is the pretext of tentpegs, and of pins for fastening together the edges of the pieces of the tent-cloth, and of the poles of the large tent? go ye forth: he who has married among you has a tent for shade from the sun:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov., and was said by a girl who had been married to a man, and whose family delayed to conduct her to her husband, urging in excuse that they had not the apparatus of the tent: she said this to urge them, and to put a stop to their excuse: (Meyd, TA: *) and the prov. is applied in attributing untruth to pretexts. (Meyd.) ―         -b2-  Hence, as being likened thereto, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A booth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shed, made of palm-sticks, and covered with"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the panic grass called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vumaAm","text_ar":"ثُمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"umbrella"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of which kings are shaded on the occasion of their riding;"},{"kind":"text","text":"called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Jator","text_ar":"چَتْر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}